%p.sg-p Combo units are used to group a pair of side-by-side elements. With <span class="sg-code">.combo.left</span> the left element occupies exactly as much space as it requires and the right elements occupies the remaining horizontal space. <span class="sg-code">.combo.right</span> is the inverse of <span class="sg-code">.combo-left</span>. The combo object is inspired by and based on the <a class="sg-a" target="_blank" href="http://www.stubbornella.org/content/2010/06/25/the-media-object-saves-hundreds-of-lines-of-code/">OOCSS Media Object</a>.

